originalText.text: My favorite part of The Lonely Entrepreneur's Learning Community is seeing and hearing all of the entrepreneur's personal and business stories on the weekly coaching calls. Its great to hear that so many business owners experience similar obstacles and it is amazing to witness the business mentoring in real time on these calls when entrepreneurs have their ah ha moment of new direction and possibility.

Michael Dermer, Victoria Sherman and Yvette Donado do not honor their contracts and refuse payment to contractors for work done. This is not an organization I would support.

Contractor beware, all "employees" are 1099 and there is a reason the hiring process is rushed.
